reviewText: As I discover that there's not a single reference to this jazz-funk ensemble's impressive body of work before "Ladies Night" (which would include the hits "Jungle Boogie" and "Hollywood Swinging") or for that matter the STILL-ubiquitous "Celebration" in any of the reviews on offer, I must speak to those who know of them before James 'JT' Taylor (and alert those who DON'T): included is what surely has to be one of the truly sickest live performances by any recording artist in history, a raging, rumbling, primal, psychotically focused but transcendent "Spirit Of The Boogie" on Don Kirschner's Rock Concert that, for a time, was posted to YouTube before being hauled down due to copyright infringement. TRUST me - it just DOESN'T get ANY funkier than THIS.....
summary: Worth it if ONLY for "Spirit Of The Boogie".....

reviewText: Most complete Kool & The Gang video collection thats out right now, including super rare videos such as Full version of "Misled", "Open Sesame", "As One", "Big Fun", "Take My Heart", "Let's Go Dancin'", "No Show", "Hi De Hi, Hi De Ho", and many other rareties as well as VH1 classic favorites such as "Fresh", "Tonight", "Joanna", "Celebration", "Cherish", and more!  From my knowledge of the late 1970's and JT Taylor era, there are two videos missing!  "Ladies Night" had a promo video in 1979 and there was no excuse for not adding that to the collection and they subed it instead for a 1981 live performance (which was great, but fans would prefer the video).  Another video thats missing from the collection was "Straight Ahead", of which came from their 1983 lp, In The Heart!  I never saw the video before, but I heard it was a wonderful video that was shot in Central Park.  It charted well in the U.K., and had minor R&B success in America!  That video should'nt have been omitted either and that kinda pissed me off!  Thats why I gave the dvd four stars.  The collection is a must get and I can't wait for Cameo, The gap Band, Shalamar, and other 1970's and 1980's R&B artists to have their own complete Videology collection soon.
summary: Most complete Kool & The Gang available, but.............
